description: The bridge you see begins at the other side from where this picture was captured. We had to walk across about 50 feet of 6 inch wide steel bar to get to the rail ties and spent about 40 minutes taking pictures on the bridge. When we spotted this small patch at the end of the bridge, we went in and found new views and flowers to play around with. When we were finished, I was walking back through the brush to get to the bridge and as I was walking, the sun was beaming through the leaves and I had to stop for a picture of the opening to the bridge. My favorite part of this photo is the sun beam.
